# /root/.claudeignore — Claude Code context-window auto-load filter
#
# Purpose (per GitHub issue #29455): tell Claude Code which files to EXCLUDE
# from automatic context loading at session start / file discovery. Prevents
# context-budget consumption + behavior-biasing from non-code artifacts.
#
# This is NOT a permissions block. Explicit Read tool calls bypass this filter
# (known limitation per GitHub issue #36163). Hard blocks belong in
# /root/.claude/settings.json `permissions.deny`. The .gitignore handles git
# tracking. The three layers are complementary:
#   .gitignore       → tracks/denies for git
#   .claudeignore    → auto-context-load filter (THIS FILE; soft)
#   permissions.deny → hard tool-access block (settings.json)
#
# Syntax: standard .gitignore globbing. Patterns are paths relative to /root.
#
# Added 2026-05-05 per operator directive: ".claudeignore... it serves another
# purpose..." — distinguishing it from permissions.deny.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Claude Code runtime artifacts (large + biasing if auto-loaded)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.claude/projects/
.claude/sessions/
.claude/file-history/
.claude/shell-snapshots/
.claude/session-env/
.claude/tasks/
.claude/backups/
.claude/cache/
.claude/history.jsonl

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. opencode runtime artifacts
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.opencode/storage/
.opencode/cache/
.opencode/state/
.opencode/logs/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Build / package caches (defensive — may not exist yet)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.cache/
.npm/
node_modules/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. Hooks runtime outputs (the hooks themselves stay tracked + auto-loadable;
#    their log files don't)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.claude/hooks/deny.log
.claude/hooks/leaks.log
.claude/hooks/malware-deny.log
**/*.log

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. Vendor binaries / downloads (when M005 modules land — defensive now)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
vendor/
vendors/
downloads/
**/*.tar.gz
**/*.tar.xz
**/*.zip
**/*.deb
**/*.pkg

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. Local-only / generated state
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.local/
.config/cache/
*.bak
*.backup
*.orig
*.swp

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Note on what's NOT in this file (and why):
#
#   /root/wiki/log/                — kept LOADED. Project history is intel,
#                                    not noise. May be revisited if log files
#                                    grow huge enough to bias context.
#   /root/wiki/backlog/            — kept LOADED. The active backlog IS the
#                                    spec; auto-context inclusion is the point.
#   /root/wiki/config/             — kept LOADED. Methodology engine.
#   /root/.claude/rules/           — kept LOADED. Agent-context rules.
#   /root/.claude/hooks/*.sh, *.py — kept LOADED. Hook scripts are spec.
#   /root/.claude/commands/        — kept LOADED. Slash command definitions.
#   /root/.claude/skills/          — kept LOADED if/when authored.
#   /root/.claude/settings.json    — kept LOADED. The hook + permissions wiring.
#
# Secrets (.env, credentials, keys) are denied by both .gitignore + the
# settings.json permissions.deny + policy-block.sh hook. Adding them here too
# would be redundant (defense-in-depth at three layers is already in place).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
